Back in 2016, John Prine was having trouble writing new songs.
Prine has been writing songs since he was 14, a skill that really took shape on his route as a mailman in suburban Illinois.
It was the first of many future interviews with Prine, and the more recent songs here pull from those later interviews.
“The Frying Pan” (1972)When I was 14, I wrote two songs that ended up on Diamonds in the Rough ten years later.
And I thought, “That’s fucked.” They should be in Washington D.C. spitting on people if they wanted to – but not the soldiers.